<p>
  <term>Reflection:</term> If you think about the operation <m>T</m> of reflecting vectors in <m>\R^2</m> about
  the line <m>y=x</m>, you can convince yourself that this is linear, and that the formula is 
  <md>
    T\left(\begin{bmatrix}x\\y\end{bmatrix}\right) = \begin{bmatrix}y\\x\end{bmatrix}.
  </md>
  Let's check this with the corresponding matrix.
</p>

